  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Slice your<strong> potatoes</strong> (skins on) into discs and add them to a baking tray (or two!) lined with <strong>tin foil</strong> with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and season with <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 15-20 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/comforting-sausage-and-apple-hotpot-with-roasted-broccoli/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick), with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Cut your <strong>sausages</strong> into rough bite-sized pieces</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sausage pieces </strong>to the pan and cook for 3-5 min or until browned all over</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/comforting-sausage-and-apple-hotpot-with-roasted-broccoli/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the sausages are browning, core and cut your <strong>apple[s]</strong> in half</p><p>Chop 2/3 into bite-sized pieces and slice the <strong>remaining apple</strong> finely (skin on)</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown</strong> <strong>onion[s]</strong></p><p>Boil half a kettle</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/comforting-sausage-and-apple-hotpot-with-roasted-broccoli/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the sausages have browned, add the <strong>sliced onion </strong>to the pan and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve your<strong> beef stock mix</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span><strong> </strong><span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and add your <strong>Henderson's Relish</strong> – this is your <strong>Henderson's stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/comforting-sausage-and-apple-hotpot-with-roasted-broccoli/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has slightly softened, add the <strong>apple pieces </strong>to the pan and cook for 2-3 min or until the apple has started to brown</p><p>Add your <strong>Chinese rice wine </strong>and cook for 30 secs or until evaporated</p><p>Stir in 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and add the <strong>Henderson's stock </strong>and<strong> </strong>cook for a further 4-5 min or until the sauce has slightly thickened, then transfer it to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> – this is your <strong>sausage & apple</strong> <strong>hotpot filling</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/comforting-sausage-and-apple-hotpot-with-roasted-broccoli/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>potato discs</strong> are done, carefully arrange them<strong> </strong>(beware, they will be hot!) and the <strong>remaining apple slices </strong>over the top of the <strong>sausage & apple hotpot filling</strong></p><p>Reserve the baking tray[s] and keep the tin foil!</p><p>Put the dish in the oven for 20-25 min or until everything is bubbling, the potatoes are golden and the sausages are cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>sausage & apple hotpot</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/comforting-sausage-and-apple-hotpot-with-roasted-broccoli/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the hotpot is in the oven, cut your<strong> broccoli </strong>into small florets, discard the stem and leaves</p><p>Add the <strong>broccoli florets</strong> to the reserved baking tray[s] with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 15 min or until beginning to char</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/comforting-sausage-and-apple-hotpot-with-roasted-broccoli/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sausage & apple hotpot</strong> with the <strong>roasted broccoli</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
